= Vote of No Confidence

The Reichstag has reconvened after its brief adjournment, prepared to address the issue of the Papen cabinet. Von Papen has lost all hope of gaining the <span style="color: #954B00;">**NSDAP**</span>'s toleration, especially after their stubborn insistence on making [+ nsdap_leader +] chancellor. All parties, except for the [? if dnvp_ideology = "Radical": <span style="color: #3F7BC1;">**DNVP**</span>?][? if dnf_formed: <span style="color: #003755;">**DNF**</span>,?][? if dvp_papen or dvp_toleration_papen: and <span style="color: var(--dvp-color);">**[+ dvp_name +]**</span> ?] have made their opposition to Papen clear, making his dismissal nearly certain.

Yet, von Papen holds a card up his sleeve. Hindenburg has already secured a decree allowing him to suspend elections beyond the constitutionally mandated 60 days. All he needs now is to present it to the Reichstag before the vote of no confidence begins.

